The paper deals with algorithms for data streams, which is a topic in computer science that falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory, as it deals with estimating frequencies of items in a stream, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of space-efficient algorithms and approximation techniques suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning), as these are common techniques used in that field. The paper also involves combinatorial and probabilistic analysis, which suggests that it may fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper deals with voting schemes and rank aggregation, which suggests that it may fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
